Outbreak timing summary

Source: R/data.R
ob_timings_summary.Rd

Summary of expected time to an outbreak under the same scenario grid, reported as median days and 95th-percentile days.

Usage

ob_timings_summary

Format

A tibble with one row per scenario:

r0

Basic reproduction number.

ve

Vaccine effectiveness (0–1).

coverage

Vaccine coverage (0–1).

chance50

Median days to outbreak.

chance95

95th-percentile days to outbreak.

Source

data-raw/ob_timings_summary.csv

Details

Larger values of chance50 and chance95 indicate slower expected outbreak timing (i.e. more time until an outbreak occurs).

See also

ob_probs_travellers, ob_summary

Examples

data(ob_timings_summary)
# typical ranges by R0
dplyr::group_by(ob_timings_summary, r0) |>
  dplyr::summarise(med = median(chance50), p95 = median(chance95))
#> # A tibble: 7 × 3
#>      r0   med   p95
#>   <dbl> <dbl> <dbl>
#> 1     3  16.4  70.6
#> 2     5 217.  947. 
#> 3     6 154.  680. 
#> 4     7 115.  498. 
#> 5     8  95.0 420. 
#> 6     9  76.7 335. 
#> 7    10  60.9 259.
